content.text:
Let me analyze the target structure and provide a detailed solution.

Analysis of the Main Target Image:
- The structure has 3 main layers
- Bottom layer: 2 yellow horizontal blocks with 3 orange cylindrical pillars between them
- Middle layer: 2 yellow horizontal blocks supporting the top structure
- Top layer: A red archway structure with an orange triangular roof

Block Count and Identification:
- 4 yellow horizontal blocks (blocks #6 or #8 or #9)
- 3 orange cylindrical pillars (block #10)
- 1 red archway piece (block #1)
- 2 orange roof triangular pieces (blocks #14 and #15)

Assembly Order:
{
    Step1: Move block with index 6 (bottom left yellow block)
    Step2: Move block with index 9 (bottom right yellow block)
    Step3: Move block with index 10 (first orange pillar)
    Step4: Move block with index 10 (second orange pillar)
    Step5: Move block with index 10 (third orange pillar)
    Step6: Move block with index 6 (middle left yellow block)
    Step7: Move block with index 9 (middle right yellow block)
    Step8: Move block with index 1 (red archway)
    Step9: Move block with index 14 (left roof triangle)
    Step10: Move block with index 15 (right roof triangle)
}

The structure is built from bottom to top, ensuring stability throughout the construction process. The yellow blocks form the foundation and middle support, the orange pillars provide vertical support, and the red archway with orange roof pieces complete the structure.
